{
  "texts": [
    "To enable policy optimization and offline analysis, DSD-Sim captures detailed performance data for processing by the Performance Analyzer.",
    "This data serves as ground truth for evaluating system performance against SLOs and as training input for AWC (Section 4).",
    "Specifically, we collect two categories of metrics:",
    "• Per-Request Metrics: Time-to-first-token (TTFT), time-per-output-token (TPOT), end-to-end latency, acceptance ratios, routing decisions, and the sequence of window size (γ) decisions.",
    "• System-Level Metrics: Overall system throughput, target device utilization, and aggregate network queueing delays."
  ]
}